Firstly, I will analyze leading Turkish stock price index (BIST 100) and popularity of finance related words on google.

1.1. Analyze BIST 100 data¶

I will use closing prices of BIST 100 index for last 6 months. Also, I will use daily data because in Turkey we experience some daily unstability in economy and I believe that on those days "BORSA ISTANBUL" fluctuates enourmusly and most people are interested in those economical unstabilities in Turkey. Therefore, financial fluctuations and trends of finance related words might be moving together for those days.

First of all we should keep in mind that we are analyzing the returns of BIST 100 index here. Therefore, those distributions can show 1. could long term investers make profit at the month (mean), 2. volatility of returns (st. dev.), 3. impacts of outlier returns (skewness). Now my comments for each month are:

  1. June:

    • We observe positive mean for returns; therefore, investing long term on BIST 100 was profitable in June.
    • In terms of volatility the best month is June. Because we observe all returns are close to each other and therefore have small variance which provides for an asset to be less risky and more predictable.
    • There is no obvious skewness for June, therefore, we would not experienced suprise (unusual positive or negative returns) if we had invested on BIST 100 in June.

  2. July:

    • We see negative mean in July; therefore, long term investors of BIST 100 have lost money.
    • There is high variance in July; therefore, the stocks were very volatile.
    • There is no obvious skewness for also July.

  3. Agust:

    • The mean is positive for Agust. Meaning that it was a profitable month.
    • In Agust BIST 100 experienced the highest variance i.e. volatility.
    • The distribution is obviously left skewed; therefore, investors have experienced bas suprises (big falls) in Agust. The worst return (-5%) of the 6 months period is experienced in Agust

  4. September:

    • There is positive mean i.e. positive profit.
    • There is low variance compared the other months. Meaning that it was not very risky to invest on BIST 100. However,
    • BIST 100 experienced left skewed distribution meaning that in some days investors lost big rates.

  5. October:

    • It seems to be 0 mean in October.
    • The variance is not too bad but,
    • It has terrible left skewness. Therefore, the investors must have lost too much money on BIST 100.

  6. November:

    • For November, BIST 100 has experienced the best mean returns.
    • Even though, we have less data for November, we can observe the volatility.
    • It seems that we are going to have left skewed data for November.

1.2. Determine the Words¶

As the third step of the analysis, I need to choose which words I will use. The first potential word is "borsa". Since I will be looking stock prices data, the closest relationship should be with "borsa" word. However, since we will be looking google trends data, it will represent the popularity among household in Turkey because it would not be rational to expect traders to use google to check the stock prices. Therefore, we can expect "dolar" and "altın" may represent financial fluctuations better as we are going to see in the analysis below.

To do the analysis of the words, I will first import data from google trends and clean the data in the code chunk below:
